cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR

This paper deals with the problem of spectrum sharing in a network of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and licensed terrestrial networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a distributed mechanism using reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the coordination of multiple agents (UAVs), which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the security threats and the need for changing operating frequencies, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of the algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
